- cs.IT (Information Theory) is likely because the paper mentions spectral gaps in moment matrices derived from solutions to sum-of-squares relaxations.
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is likely because the paper involves analyzing the running times of algorithms and establishing small spectral gaps.
